{{Quote|Nothing can stop us now! The glory of the Hiromi is assured! Yaayyy!|Hirog, during the invasion of [[Zeltros/Legends|Zeltros]]|<ref name="Nagais and Dolls">[[Star Wars (1977) 104|''Star Wars'' (1977) 104]]</ref>}}
The '''Hiromi''' were a bipedal, [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]], [[Insectoid/Legends|insectoid]] [[Species/Legends|species]]. Despite a strong instinct for self-preservation and a large aversion to anything that could bring them harm, the Hiromi saw themselves as a glorious race of mighty warriors. Their government was the [[Hiromi Empire]], and they were members of the [[Alliance of Free Planets]]. The Hiromi secretly dreamt of [[The galaxy/Legends|galactic]] conquest; to achieve their aims, shortly after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]] they tried to incite a war between [[Lahsbane/Legends|Lahsbane]] and the [[Ewok/Legends|Ewoks]] to tear the Alliance apart, but this plot was foiled. They then tried [[Operation: Glorious Destiny|to conquer]] [[Zeltros/Legends|Zeltros]], but were again foiled when the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] was later [[Battle of Zeltros|conquered]] by the [[Nagai/Legends|Nagai]], and in turn the [[Tof/Legends|Tofs]]. They gave up their dreams of conquest afterwards, helping the Alliance and the Nagai [[Nagai–Tof War|fight]] the Tofs.

==Biology and appearance==
Hiromi were a [[Color/Legends|green]], [[Insect/Legends|insectoid]] [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Species/Legends|species]]<ref name="Small Wars" /> approximately 1.5 [[Meter/Legends|meters]] tall.<ref name="CSWE" /> They had yellow [[Eye/Legends|eyes]], two long antennae on their heads, and unlike many insectoid species, tongues.<ref name="Small Wars" />

All Hiromi serving in their invasion force were clad in a uniform of red berets and boots, with the exception of [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Hookyr]], who wore a red hat.<ref name="Small Wars" /> They dressed in red, tan, and purple attire.<ref name="CSWE" />

==Society and culture==
{{Quote|Let's hear it for not getting hurt!|Captain Hookyr|<ref name="My Hiromi">[[Star Wars (1977) 106|''Star Wars'' (1977) 106]]</ref>}}
The most prominent trait of the Hiromi was their instinct for self-preservation.<ref name="Planet Hoppers">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20040105zeltros1|series=Zeltros: Pleasure Planet|text=Part 1: Who Doesn't Like Zeltrons?}}</ref> One of their favorite activities was, in their words, "not getting beaten up". The Hiromi became very fearful when the possibility of being in danger came up, and were quick to suggest alternatives to fighting&mdash;including bringing in reinforcements to fight in their stead, hiding, and going home. Nonetheless, when they were truly needed, the Hiromi charged headlong into whatever task was required of them, though they were no less afraid as they did so.<ref name="My Hiromi" />

[[File:HiromiCheer.jpg|thumb|left|The Hiromi enjoyed cheering.]]
The Hiromi had a grandiose image of themselves, claiming to be "glorious conquerors,"<ref name="The Party's Over">[[Star Wars (1977) 105|''Star Wars'' (1977) 105]]</ref> though their short attention spans meant that their grand long-term plans, such as [[The galaxy/Legends|galactic]] control, were frequently derailed by thoughts of food or play.<ref name="CSWE" /> The [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] would observe that they enjoyed the work of conquest.<ref name="Nagais and Dolls" /> Other words they used to describe themselves included "glorious", "ruthless", and "supreme". Hiromi considered themselves to be ruthless masters of interrogation, and backed this claim up by making subjects crack in a short time by relentlessly bombarding them with shouts of "Talk!".<ref name="My Hiromi" />

Another activity the Hiromi enjoyed greatly was cheering.<ref name="My Hiromi" /> Whenever they achieved any kind of victory, they would praise themselves and let out a cheer. This was, to them, a very important part of any activity.<ref name="Nagais and Dolls" /> When Luke Skywalker sought to rally the Hiromi, he appealed to their love of cheering by leading them in one.<ref name="My Hiromi" />

Finally, the Hiromi had a great passion for food.<ref name="My Hiromi" /> Their first task after "conquering" Zeltros was to have lunch, and they had nothing but praise for the quality of the Zeltronian food and [[Doughnut/Legends|desserts]].<ref name="Nagais and Dolls" /> The Hiromi knew of the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] and [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] only through legends.<ref name="Small Wars" />

==History==
==="The glorious destiny of the Hiromi"===
{{Quote|Perhaps the glorious destiny of the Hiromi would be best served if we were to strategically withdraw&hellip;at once!|Hiromi [[Commander/Legends|Commander]], following the loss on Endor|<ref name="Small Wars" />}}
[[File:Kuratcha.jpg|thumb|right|The ''Kuratcha'', a starship of distinctive Hiromi design.]]
Approximately [[2000 BBY/Legends|2000 years]] before the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], the Hiromi Empire began planning its conquest of the galaxy. Over the next two millennia they watched the shape of galactic affairs and waited in hiding. They heard legends of the Jedi Knights and their powers, though it would not be until their invasion that they saw one, namely Luke Skywalker, in action.<ref name="Small Wars" />

In [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], shortly after the Battle of Endor,<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> the Hiromi mothership ''[[Kuratcha]]'' was dispatched as part of the advanced force of the invasion of the [[Galaxy/Legends|galaxy]], and the Hiromi operative [[Hirog]] infiltrated the command staff of the [[Alliance of Free Planets]] as [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Ackbar's]] aide. Hirog's mission was to destabilize the Alliance to prepare for the Hiromi invasion, which he set about doing by pitting the [[Lahsbee/Huhk|Lahsbee]] and [[Ewok/Legends|Ewoks]] at war against each other, as these were considered to be the two least dangerous members of the Alliance.<ref name="Small Wars" />

[[File:Hirog-bomb.jpg|thumb|left|Hirog prepares his bomb.]]
The first phase of his plot was to arrange it to appear that one of the Lahsbee was engaging in an affair with the Ewok [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Kamida]]. The Ewok [[Tippet/Legends|Tippet]], who had been courting her, was outraged, and began rallying his people to fight the Lahsbee. The second phase of the Hiromi plan was to plant a bomb near the Alliance leadership; when it detonated, it would kill all the participants in the conflict, leaving the rest of the galaxy to assume it was the fault of either the Lahsbee or the Ewoks. With the leaders of the Alliance dead, their worlds would presumably split and wage war on each other.<ref name="Small Wars" />

The situation never reached this point. A stray [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] shot, accidentally fired during an honor duel between the Lahsbee and Tippet, disabled the timing mechanism on Hirog's bomb, causing it to tick uncontrollably towards detonation. Hirog ran screaming from his hiding place, yelling to everyone present about the plans of the Hiromi and their impending doom. As it happened, one of the Lahsbee had transformed into their animalistic form, the Huhk, and when the creature flung a rock at Hirog and missed, it accidentally disabled the bomb. The Hiromi forces on the mothership chose to abandon Hirog and retreated, the Ewoks and Lahsbee made peace, and Hirog was chased from the scene by the enraged Huhk.<ref name="Small Wars" /> He somehow escaped, and later rejoined the Hiromi forces.<ref name="Nagais and Dolls" />

===The invasion of Zeltros===
{{Quote|My initial recommendation: Cancel the invasion of Zeltros and try a world that's less populated. Perhaps even unpopulated.|Ensign Phoebe|<ref name="Planet Hoppers" />}}
[[File:Hiromi_YAAYYY.jpg|thumb|right|The Hiromi conquest of the Zeltros throne room]]
Not to be defeated, the Hiromi next set their sights upon the world of Zeltros, home of the [[Zeltron/Legends|Zeltrons]]. Captain Hookyr, leader of the invasion force, decided that with its temperate climate and rich supply of pleasures, Zeltros was the perfect world for their people. Arriving in orbit on the ''Kuratcha'', they dispatched a force to the royal palace. Members of the Alliance of Free Planets had come to Zeltros too, and [[King/Legends|King]] [[Arno (Zeltron)|Arno]] and [[Queen/Legends|Queen]] [[Leonie]] held a party for them. With the king and queen busy reveling, and many Zeltros drunk, Hiromi scout [[Ensign/Legends|Ensign]] [[Phoebe]] reported that they had been neutralized, and recommended the Hiromi strike. The rest of the invasion force, meanwhile, "captured" Luke Skywalker and the [[Hoojib/Legends|Hoojib]] [[Plif/Legends|Plif]], though in fact Skywalker had allowed himself to be taken to see whether the Hiromi had the backing of any stronger allies.<ref name="Nagais and Dolls" />

This accomplished, the invaders then swept into the empty throne room, and, with the Hiromi declaring him "Hookyr the First", the ruler of Zeltros, Captain Hookyr took his seat on the Zeltron throne. By his order, the first act of the Hiromi was to go to the royal kitchen and have lunch.<ref name="Nagais and Dolls" /> Unfortunately for them, two other parties had arrived on Zeltros, the Nagai and the Tofs, each of them determined to [[Battle of Zeltros|conquer]] the world first. The Tof broke their way into the kitchen and took the Hiromi invaders captive.<ref name="The Party's Over" /> Altogether, the Hiromi conquest of the palace kitchen was the shortest successful invasion of Zeltros ever recorded.<ref name="Planet Hoppers" />

===Heroes of the Alliance===
{{Quote|Captain Hookyr believes that keeping the peace between the Hiromi and the Alliance is in the end a better solution than being chopped into pieces. I must say I agree.|Hirog|<ref name="Planet Hoppers" />}}
[[File:Hiromi_interrogation.jpg|thumb|left|upright|The Hiromi interrogate their Tof prisoner.]]
Skywalker and the Hoojibs, although taken captive by the Tof, did not remain so for long, and after defeating their captors they freed the Hiromi.<ref name="The Party's Over" /> Four Zeltron friends of Skywalker had been captured by the Tof, and Skywalker enlisted the help of the Hiromi to rescue them from the Tof ship. Though initially frightened, the Hiromi saw it as another chance to fulfill their destiny. Skywalker then turned their interrogation skills against a Tof prisoner, who quickly cracked and told them the codes to infiltrate the Tof vessel in [[Orbit/Legends|orbit]].<ref name="My Hiromi" />

Taking the ''Kuratcha'' to the Tof [[Wayfarer (Tof starship)|''Wayfarer'']], the Hiromi waited in the ship until Skywalker had dispatched the guards in the hangar. While they wanted to stay beside Skywalker as he sabotaged the Tof ship, Skywalker heaped praise upon, as he said, "that dauntless, matchless, legendary Hiromi spirit", and thus inspired the Hiromi to charge off to rescue the prisoners. However, it was not as simple as they expected; the Zeltrons believed the Hiromi were working with their captors and assaulted them, and only the timely arrival of Skywalker saved them. A Tof, meanwhile, began sneaking up on Skywalker; Hirog shouted a warning and shot the Tof, killing him. Having killed a Tof in a fair fight for the first time, the Hiromi were very pleased with themselves, and the gathered party let out a loud cheer.<ref name="My Hiromi" /> Later, the Hiromi would muse that Skywalker had only helped a little, and that it had been them who had truly helped defeat the Tofs.<ref name="Planet Hoppers" />

In the wake of their victory. the crew of the ''Kuratcha'' put in a request to return home. They believed they could best serve the Alliance and the Hiromi while safely hidden&mdash;though they were careful to explain that this did not mean they were afraid.<ref name="Planet Hoppers" />

==Hiromi in the galaxy==
{{Quote|Let's hear it for the ruthless Hiromi!|A Hiromi interrogator|<ref name="My Hiromi" />}}
[[File:Hookyr.jpg|thumb|right|Hookyr, the commander of the ''Kuratcha'']]
Although the Hiromi had plans for conquest since two millennia before the time of the Rebellion, they did not put these plans into action until after the Battle of Endor. However, the Rebel Alliance had known of the Hiromi for long enough that Hirog had time to cultivate a trusted position as Ackbar's aide.<ref name="Small Wars" />

After their plot was uncovered, the Alliance still did not take the Hiromi seriously as a threat. During their invasion of Zeltros, Luke Skywalker even let himself be taken by them, not fearing that they could do him or anybody any harm, and finding their attempts at conquest humorous.<ref name="Nagais and Dolls" /> After their unsuccessful bid at galactic domination, the Hiromi made peace with and briefly fought alongside the Alliance of Free Planets, before retreating to their homeworld to wait out the rest of the [[Nagai–Tof War]].<ref name="Planet Hoppers" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|The Hiromi were just a blast, so convinced they were so smart and evil and deadly....and such utter, craven buffoons. I loved whenever we could work them in [&hellip;]|Mary Jo Duffy, ''Star Wars Insider'' 151|<ref name="Red Five (department)">{{InsiderCite|151|Red Five|Red Five: Jo Duffy}}</ref>}}
Author [[Mary Jo Duffy]] created the Hiromi while she was the head writer of [[Marvel Comics]]' ongoing [[Star Wars (1977)|''Star Wars'' series]] of [[Star Wars comic books|comics]] in [[1985]]. Duffy named the Hiromi after Japanese musician [[Wikipedia:Go Hiromi|Go Hiromi]].<ref name="Comic Marvels">{{InsiderCite|91|Comic Marvels}}</ref> Hiromi skin color varies between reddish-brown and green throughout their appearances in the comics. By the end of their run in the Marvel series, they were green, and as their most recent appearance this is assumed to be the most accurate portrayal. An alien resembling a Hiromi appears in the [[Knights of the Old Republic 13|thirteenth issue]] of the [[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic (comic series)|''Knights of the Old Republic'']] comic series, published in [[2007]], but it is unclear if it is in fact a Hiromi.

